<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36130g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36130g">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36130g"> 130(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Fitz-Ailwyne&apos;s Assize</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">These <font color="green">[London]</font> houses <font color="green">[built of wood and with straw thatch]</font> were specially liable to be destroyed by fire, and in order to save the city from this imminent danger the famous Assize of Building known as &ldquo;<mark>Fitz-Ailwyne&apos;s Assize</mark>&rdquo; was drawn up in 1189. <small> &ldquo;LONDON&rdquo; <a name="EBLO" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBLO"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 959d</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
